To work around this issue, I have to do the following currently:

1. Wrap my TextField with a RawKeyboardListener, see below for onKey method handleRawKey
2. Remove onEditingComplete from TextField otherwise focus changes when pressing enter
3. Use keyboardType: TextInputType.text and textInputAction: TextInputAction.unspecified in my TextField

onKey event to manually register new lines:

```
void handleRawKey(RawKeyEvent key) {
  if (key.isShiftPressed &&
        LogicalKeyboardKey.enter.keyId == key.logicalKey.keyId &&
        key.character != null) {
      textEditingController.value = TextEditingValue(
          text: '${textEditingController.text}\n',
          selection:
              TextSelection.collapsed(offset: textEditingController.text.length + 1));
      return;
    }
}
```

